            "type": "h2-post",
            "content": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The <b><i>Futur I</i></b> tense is used in German to talk about actions or events that will happen in the future. While the present tense is often used for near-future events, Futur I is used to emphasize that an action will definitely take place at a future time."
        },
        {
            "type": "callout",
            "content": "The <b><i>Futur I</i></b> tense is not very important in the German language and is not critical to learn, but you must still learn it. Good news is that it is very easy!"
        },
        {
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Usage"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "We use the <i>Perfekt</i> tense to express:"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Expressing Future Intentions or Plans:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Ich werde morgen einkaufen gehen",
                            "text": "Example: Ich <b>werde</b> morgen einkaufen $__gehen-gehen[verb-link-hover]__$ ",
                            "translation": "(I will go shopping tomorrow.)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Making Predictions or Assumptions about the Future:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Es wird morgen regnen.",
                            "text": "Es <b>wird</b> morgen $__regnen-regnen[verb-link-hover]__$.",
                            "translation": "(It will rain tomorrow)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Expressing Promises or Assurances:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Ich werde dir helfen",
                            "text": "Ich <b>werde</b> dir $__helfen-helfen[verb-link-hover]__$.",
                            "translation": "(I will help you)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Speculating about the Present or the Future:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Er wird jetzt zu Hause sein.",
                            "text": "Er <b>wird</b> jetzt zu Hause $__sein-sein[verb-link-hover]__$.",
                            "translation": "(He will be at home now)"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Conjugation"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The <i>Futur I</i> tense is formed with the <b>present</b> tense of the auxiliary verb <b>\"werden\"</b> and the <b>infinitive</b> of the main verb. Here's how to conjugate \"werden\" in the present tense:"
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "table": {
                "audio": "ich werde, du wirst, (er) (sie) (es) wird, wir werden, ihr werdet, sie werden.",
                "headings": ["person", "sein"],
                "rows": [
                    ["ich", "<span>werd<i>e</i></span>"],
                    ["du", "<span>w<u>ir</u><i>st</i></b></span>"],
                    ["er/sie/es", "<span>w<u>ir</u><i>d</i></span>"],
                    ["wir", "<span>werd<i>en</i></span>"],
                    ["ihr", "<span>werd<i>et</i></span>"],
                    ["Sie", "<span>werd<i>en</i></span>"]
                ]
            }
        },
